<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - OIL PAN, VIBRATION DAMPER, OIL
        PUMP, WATER PUMP, AND FRONT COVER - Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Vibration Damper Wear Sleeve</title>
            <figure id="f1200520" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg2/eg2599.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Installing the Vibration Damper Wear Sleeve</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Wear Sleeve Installation Tool</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Wear Sleeve</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Loctite&#174; #271</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Vibration Damper</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Press</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Make sure the vibration damper is clean and free of oil before installing the wear sleeve.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply Loctite&#174; #271 around the circumference of the wear sleeve. Place the wear
                    sleeve onto the wear sleeve installation tool.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the wear sleeve in the installation tool so the outer chamfer is facing toward
                    the tool.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the installation tool on a press table. Position the vibration damper over the
                    wear sleeve installation tool and lower the damper onto the wear sleeve installation tool.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a press to apply pressure to the inner member of the vibration damper until the
                    installation tool bottoms out or seats.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
